<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.276.2" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/1536" speakername="Patrick McLoughlin" colnum="276"  time="010:34:00" url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200506/cmhansrd/cm050519/debtext/50519-03.htm#50519-03_spnew6">
	<p pid=".276.2/1">Towards the end of the last Parliament the Government accepted in the Modernisation Committee that we should be able to table written questions during the summer recess. As the Leader of the House has today announced that the summer recess will be longer than was originally planned, will he ensure that there is an opportunity for the relevant motion to be laid so that those of us who wish to hold the Government to account, even during the summer recess, have that opportunity?</p>
</speech>
<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.276.3" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19a.276.3" matchtype="perfectmatch"/>
<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.276.4" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19a.276.4" matchtype="perfectmatch"/>
<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.277.0" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19a.277.0" matchtype="perfectmatch"/>
<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.277.1" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19a.277.1" matchtype="perfectmatch"/>
<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.277.2" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19a.277.2" matchtype="perfectmatch"/>
<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.277.3" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19a.277.3" matchtype="changes"/>
<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.277.3" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/1398" speakername="Alistair Burt" colnum="277"  time="010:34:00" url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200506/cmhansrd/cm050519/debtext/50519-03.htm#50519-03_spnew12">
	<p pid=".277.3/1">Will the Leader of the House arrange for an early debate on the Government's failure to take key strategic decisions, in particular on the full fitting-out of the St. Pancras international rail station to allow proper access to other rail and underground services? The delay is not only threatening severe inconvenience and disruption, but also suggests a lack of commitment to infrastructure in an increasingly overcrowded, at Government instigation, south-east of England. Would a debate on these failures to take key decisions set our minds at rest?</p>
</speech>
<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.277.4" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19a.277.4" matchtype="perfectmatch"/>
<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.278.0" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19a.278.0" matchtype="perfectmatch"/>
<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.278.1" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19a.278.1" matchtype="perfectmatch"/>
<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.278.2" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19a.278.2" matchtype="perfectmatch"/>
<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.278.3" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19a.278.3" matchtype="perfectmatch"/>
<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.278.4" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19a.278.4" matchtype="perfectmatch"/>
<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.278.5" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19a.278.5" matchtype="perfectmatch"/>
