<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.278.6" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/1422" speakername="Andrew Robathan" colnum="278"  time="010:34:00" url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200506/cmhansrd/cm050519/debtext/50519-04.htm#50519-04_spnew2">
	<p pid=".278.6/1">Given the Leader of the House's former appointment as Defence Secretary, I know that he will be as concerned as I am about the fact that it is likely that fewer than half of servicemen and servicewomen were registered to vote in the general election this year. Not only that, but those who were registered to vote in Iraq, Afghanistan or wherever by post, had no opportunity to return those votes. Will he instigate an inquiry into how many people were registered to vote and how may people were able to vote, and ensure that next time an election comes up our servicemen and women in places of danger, serving this country, have the opportunity to vote properly?</p>
</speech>
<gidredirect oldgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19.278.7" newgid="uk.org.publicwhip/debate/2005-05-19a.278.7" matchtype="perfectmatch"/>
